"v.足够，(食物)满足 【英】 v.足够，(食物)满足( to meet or satisfy a need) 【记】 suf(下面)＋fice(做) →做出来→足够 【例】 One glass suffices me.(我一杯就够) v. 足够; (食物)满足 【记】读: 三face, 一个人长了三张脸－足够 【记】sufficient suffice (v.)  early 14c. (intransitive); late 14c. (transitive), from present participle stem of Old French sofire ""be sufficient, satisfy"" (Modern French suffire), from Latin sufficere ""put under, lay a foundation under; supply as a substitute; be enough, be adequate,"" from sub ""up to"" (see sub-) + root of facere ""to make"" (see factitious). Phrase suffice it to say (1690s) is a rare surviving subjunctive."
